                </pullquote_e2b2>
                <textonlycomponent_b4
                    jcr:created="{Date}2018-06-18T09:18:06.257-07:00"
                    jcr:createdBy="velazquez@hpe.com"
                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2019-04-15T15:06:58.314Z"
                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="christine.seales@hpe.com"
                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                    sling:resourceType="hpeweb/components/content/textOnlyComponent"
                    textOnly="&lt;p>&lt;span class=&quot;body-copy-large&quot;>HPE led the design and implementation of the back-end system and supported Saudi Payments, to help them choose the right technology so that members of the public can easily make payments and purchases through their smartphones. After originally starting as a proof of concept using HPE Synergy as a lab, the system went live in May 2018.&lt;br>&#xa;&lt;br>&#xa;Abdullah Altammami, Infrastructure Manager from the Saudi Payments said, “HPE has been a real partner from the test stage to project completion and the team’s commitment, tenacity and flexibility has made them an ideal partner as we successfully introduced contactless mobile payments to the Saudi Arabian market for the first time”.&lt;br>&#xa;&lt;br>&#xa;Issa Alkhames, Managing Director, KSA from HPE said, “As the Saudi market sees significant digital transformation as part of its Vision 2030, we were delighted to be selected by Saudi Payments as its partner to create a sustainable solution which provides consumers in Saudi Arabia with greater choice through access to contactless mobile payments.”&lt;/span>&lt;/p>&#xa;"
                    topPadding="30"/>
